<file path="design-context/01_concept.md">
# Developer Progression Portfolio

This is not a traditional portfolio.

It is an interactive gamified experience where the user scrolls to progress through the developer’s career.

## Core idea

- Scroll = experience gain
- Experience = XP system
- XP = level progression
- Level = unlocks skills and milestones

The interface behaves like a game HUD.

## Main UI concept

A fixed Profile HUD card displays:

- Name
- Role
- Level
- XP bar
- Unlocked skills, and level increments when repeating skills, creating a dynamic skill badge system that visually represents the developer's expertise and experience in each skill.

The rest of the page is a scroll-driven timeline of milestones.
</file>

<file path="design-context/02_visual-system.md">
# Visual System

## Style direction

- Dark mode (deep navy / black base)
- Futuristic SaaS dashboard aesthetic, rounded corners, smooth gradients
- 3D-inspired UI elements with subtle depth
- Subtle glow accents (blue / purple)
- Glassmorphism panels
- Clean typography (Inter / JetBrains Mono)

## UI components style

- Cards: glass + soft border + blur
- Buttons: minimal, glowing hover
- Progress bars: smooth gradient fill
- Icons: consistent simple icon set (Simple Icons / Lucide style)

## Avoid

- Hacker modern terminal style IA inspiration
- Over-glitch effects
- Heavy neon saturation
</file>

<file path="design-context/03_interaction-model.md">
# Interaction Model

## Scroll system

Scroll drives all progression:

scrollProgress (0 → 1) controls:

- XP accumulation
- Level progression
- Milestone unlocking
- Skill unlocking

## Behavior rules

- Profile HUD is always visible (sticky)
- Milestones appear sequentially on scroll
- XP bar animates smoothly
- Level updates when thresholds are reached
- Skills unlock progressively

## Animation rules

- All transitions must be smooth (300–800ms)
- Use easing (no linear animations)
- XP updates must feel continuous, not discrete
</file>

